        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>Rule 6.21.  Bill read by clauses
In the Committee of the Whole a motion to proceed &quot;seriatim&quot; shall be in order and when carried the effect thereof shall be that each legislative instrument referred thereto shall be read and debated by clauses, except that the title thereof shall be considered last.
Mason's Manual:  Sec. 113
HR 3, 1973.</p>
